      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder,

Allow me to be the first to congratulate you on resolving the situation at the [url=glossary:burning library]Burning Library[/url]. You should see Fatebinder Rhogalus vie against himself: half of him reels at the sheer loss of tomes historical and magical, yet he cannot contain his glee at hearing that the Sages have been finally and entirely broken. 

I do not share his loathing of the old School. They built their own pyre on their hubris, true, but my opposition to them remains purely professional. To have the old [url=glossary:vellum citadel]Vellum Citadel[/url] truly destroyed - my eyes burn at the secrets that met the flame. Comfort comes when I remember that an ambitious Fatebinder would have preserved a few choice pieces of lore, perhaps as much as they could carry out.

I hope you soon make an effort to join us at Court in the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url]. I often feel that it has been too long since we last whispered of the darker corners of Terratus. You've experienced so many of them as of late. Perhaps I can provide illumination.

- Calio
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
