      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder,

Allow me to be the first to congratulate you on resolving the situation at the [url=glossary:burning library]Burning Library[/url]. Fatebinder Rhogalus could not be more pleased by your choice to preserve the texts and relics of the old Sages. Or perhaps he's overjoyed that their grip on the library is now entirely broken. In either case, he almost borders on giddy. Almost.

I do not share his loathing of the old Guild. They built their own pyre on their hubris, true, but my opposition to them remains purely professional. It gladdens me that not their every myriad secret met the flame. I even suspect that an ambitious Fatebinder would have collected a few stray scraps of lore, perhaps as much as they could carry out.

I hope you soon make an effort to join us at Court in the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url]. I often feel that it has been too long since we last whispered of the darker corners of Terratus. You've experienced so many of them as of late. Perhaps I can provide illumination.

- Calio</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder,

I suspect I need never again impress upon you the gravity of our role in the Overlord's great work. One can condemn a man who murders for a few rings with a clean conscience. More difficult by far is recognition of the need to end the life of a mother and child. I do not envy you your assignment.

I imagine that, whatever demeanor he adopts, the Archon of War will remember your choice until one of you finds your way to the void.

I hope you soon make an effort to join us at Court in the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url]. I often feel that it has been too long since we last whispered of the darker corners of Terratus. You've experienced so many of them as of late. Perhaps I can provide illumination.

- Calio</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder,

You have proven your cleverness in the face of an apparently impossible choice. Would I have been so wise in the same situation? I cannot say. I know only that I do not envy your mission.

I must urge caution, however: some who watch your actions may be more alarmed than amused. Will they be able to convince themselves that the Overlord crafted the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Storms with this loophole in mind? Or will they see in your choice an alternative that cannot be set to parchment?

I hope you soon make an effort to join us at Court in the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url]. I often feel that it has been too long since we last whispered of the darker corners of Terratus. You've experienced so many of them as of late. Perhaps I can provide illumination.

- Calio</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder,

Or should I address you as "Governor?"

One wonders how often in history a garrison has been empowered to protect an area only to be broken and scattered by the very individual who granted their authority. You take as freely as you give, it seems. 

It certainly lends you a particular mystique. I have no doubt it will become a cornerstone of the stories told of you. I try to avoid attracting too many stories myself, but far be it for me to tell you how to pursue your objectives.

I hope you soon make an effort to join us at Court in the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url]. I often feel that it has been too long since we last whispered of the darker corners of Terratus. You've experienced so many of them as of late. Perhaps I can provide illumination.

- Calio</DefaultText>
