      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder,

So many intersting stories have begun to circle around you: they say you have locked blades with madmen, overcome howling swarms of Magebane, and even, despite the strictures of the Overlord, claimed artifacts from the shadowed depths of the Oldwalls.

You seem to woo attention with the ardency of a newlywed. I try to avoid attracting too many stories myself, but far be it for me to tell you how to pursue your objectives.

I hope you soon make an effort to join us at Court in the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url]. I often feel that it has been too long since we last whispered of the darker corners of Terratus. You've experienced so many of them as of late. Perhaps I can provide illumination.

- Calio</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder,

Straydus Herodin's blood stains the flagstones of Sentinel Stand and Chorus crimson drapes from its crenels, yet the Overlord's [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Storms rages still, as if to spite the Archon of War and frustrate his claims on the peninsula.

Weigh your actions with care. In the pursuit of his ambitions, [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url] may seem to twist the Overlord's will with impunity, but [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url]'s reckoning often comes when one expects it least.

This missive turned out much more dire than I intended!

I hope you soon make an effort to join us at Court in the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url]. I often feel that it has been too long since we last whispered of the darker corners of Terratus. You've experienced so many of them as of late. Perhaps I can provide illumination.

- Calio</DefaultText>
